column6: 26 years old and this is only the second pair of Lululemon leggings I’ve purchased. At my age, the price isn’t ideal but a younger friend of mine has every color, every shade, and every pattern of the wunder unders (I’m exaggerating but you get the point). I always tell her how amazing they look on her and she keeps telling me I need a pair. Me being 10 years older- I assume they look good on her cause she’s young and active. But whatever I break down and spend 100 dollars on the basic black wunder unders. Darn. They’re so amazing that it’s upsetting. But then... I break down and by another pair (these babies)...game changer. They’re not only so cute but they’re warm and compress everything beautifully. As someone on the curvier side- I don’t have the confidence to wear leggings without constantly making sure something is covering my bottom, but these make me feel so good and fit. The thicker material makes the fit tighter but they are so flattering! I love them so much and am already ready for my next pair...
I have been dying to get a pair of these in the dark black and they have been out of stock. Please bring them back I love them!

column5: The only good ones are Variegated Knit Brushed Luon Black Heathered Black
column6: Out of these knit-type WUs, he only true old-quality are Variegated Knit Brushed Luon Black Heathered Black -- no wonder they are almost gone. They are thick and compressive, perfect for winter. I bought them last year, go to a very sweaty yoga three times a week and sweat in those at least once a week and they hold up wonderfully. (Yes, the color is grey, not black, but the quality beats it). Rush Jacquard Black White are good too, but they are thin, good for the summer, but not right now. Luon Variegated Knit Black Heathered Black are plain sucks -- thin, no compression, and unpleasant somewhat plastic feel of the fabric, I returned them right away. Lulu, please make for winter some more solid colors in that Variegated Knit Brushed Luon fabric that is almost gone, you used to make purple in those! And old-fashioned Skinny Wills please! (not Skinny Grooves, those are horrible btw).

After looking through these reviews, I wanted to add my own thoughts specifically about the knit-style Wunder Unders. I bought a pair last year, and they are my FAVORITE. I would say that because they are knit, they are a little different than regular luon: softer, thicker, and they just look super cool. I do CrossFit and I don't wear them for my toughest/messiest workouts (because they are too nice), but I do wear them for less intense work (e.g., stretching, running, coaching...). Mostly, they are my favorite general purpose "athletic" leggings. I think the knit style makes them look a little classier, so I will wear them to work, out and about, or just to lounge at home. I receive a lot of compliments on them. I've worn them at least weekly for a year, and no problems so far.

column6: I had decided to try out the luon fabric after being an avid align pant buyer. At first, these pants fit pretty well even though I had to size up so that they would not be see through when bending over. Sadly within three days there was already pilling on the inner thighs which I have been used to in most leggings. The thing I was shocked by was the fuzziness that came over the rest of the leggings even after only handwashing and air drying them. Not to mention a hole started to form in one of the pairs plus they would no longer stay up! I would way rather recommend buying some of the knitted luon ones that actually stay up and are not see through even in the lighter colors. Wish I could have discovered that before throwing these to the bottom of my drawer.

column6: I own 7 pairs of Lululemon leggings and these are by far my least favorite. They are extremely tight though they are the same size as all of my other leggings. The fabric does not feel $100 worthy, and after owning them for over a year I have probably worn them twice. They are not comfortable nor very flattering. If you are going to spend this kind of money on leggings, I would recommend the Align Pant II over these any day.

column6: I wanted to love these leggings, but I don't. When in store, I tried on the size 6 and 8. Both myself and the store associate agreed that the size 6 looked see-through when I bent over. I tried on the 8 and they seemed to fit well, not see through and the associate agreed that they seemed like my size. Well... after one wear to the gym I cannot imagine wearing these to any physical activity. THEY FALL DOWN. I was constantly pulling them up. Worst part.. my friend at the gym said they were a bit see through when bending over to do lifts. I am so disappointed. When spending $100 +tax I expected better quality and fit.

column6:
I usually don’t pay much attention to super negative lulu reviews. However, what people are saying about the newest luon material is true. I'm quite disappointed in these tights. I bought them because I knew luon was the thickest tight fabric, and I wanted to use these for winter to wear under a long sweater/cardigan, etc.
I also loved the juniper colour.
However, these ones are much thinner than my old ones and the weave must be different because when I bend over, these ones are see through. You can see the tag and writing at the back of the pant. Sizing up makes no difference.
Thankfully, lulu is great at customer service and I am able to return these, despite having purchased them on WMTM (thank-you!)

I bought incognito Camo Multi Grey, since i really liked this design i bought one at store and one on online shop (for gift). I've been using this carefully, no dryer, cold water washing, hang dry. After i wore this ONLY 3 weeks, it was getting pills and I'm so disappointed. I bought 20Y collection wonder under too, but it seems like different fabric. So sad i really like this Incognito Camo Multi Grey design but material is poor

column6: Thought they were supperrrr cute! I love them soooooo much!

I have been wearing Lulu leggings for about 7 years (I actually still wear my original pair) and I bought these ones made of the new fabric a few months ago. I love the material so much more than the old ones and I love the fit of the high rise. I have only washed them a few times and haven't notice any pilling. I don't find them see through at all unlike some of the other reviewers. My sister tried on a pair and found them a bit sheer but she really just needed to go up a size, so I recommend trying them on before buying. I find them completely true to size but my sister is between sizes so it was a bit more important for her to try them on first!
column14: high rise is the perfect height

column6: These use to be my go to pants, especially for dance class, but I don't know what has happened to them in past years because they are so THIN. My older pairs still feel like better quality than these ones. I literally bought them today and didn't try them on because I've been the same size for ever and you can literally read the hang tag when you bend over.

column6: I was really excited to buy these pants this February because the Lululemon brand comes so highly recommended. The brand itself has a excellent reputation and all my friends that I asked recommended them to me. They told me how they've had their Lululemon products, the pants, sports bras and other things, for years. I was hesitating to spend so much money on one pair of yoga pants, but people assured me it was a good investment and I would wear them for years to come. When I first got the pants I was excited because they fit so well, looked good and were perfectly high-waisted for me but when I worked out in them I noticed the material was not opaque. My skin showed through when I would squat or stretch. I have only washed them three times in the seven months I've had them and have washed them according to instructions, with cold water, low tumble, and air dry them, but after the second time I washed them I noticed pilling along the waist and butt area. I am disappointed in the product, I expected better quality especially considering how expensive they are.

column6: Can’t go to college without them

I didn't try them on in store since I have been the same size for years...big mistake. The material is thin, and definitely does not pass the squat test. I could see the rip tag when I bent over. And yes, they are the right size, there is material bunching at my crotch. I will be returning and honestly, I might just try and find a new go-to for workout wear...

column6: Love the color and the fit and the style - basically everything about it- but they were a bit too high rise for me. I’ll still wear them everywhere!!

For me, these pants are as good as it gets. Of note, I'm 5'8 with a 35" inseam and weigh about 145, and do Ashtanga primary and a wee bit of secondary. I'm pretty bendy. I appreciate that these things stay in place for some of the more contorted poses like Bhuja Pidasana and the Mariciasanas. They are long enough that I can get my arms through my lotus for Garha Pindasana. The pants don't bind - I've had some where the seam digs into my belly, and they don't bunch up around the knees. I wash in cold and line dry and they seem to be holding up just fine. If you are relatively new or thinking, "I have no idea what that woman just said," A) keep at it, you will! and B) Good, comfortable gear helps immensely, and I think this is the good stuff.
I like these leggings but they are really thick. Will be nice for the winter but for summer a little too thick to wear to workout. Really comfy and soft though!
These are so great for so many things. I'm a full-time student and cycling instructor- these pants take me from school to sweat seamlessly!

Amazing feel and fit. I love these leggings. The only problem is they do not last as long as the other lulu lemon leggings I have. I have had some for 5 or more years. These I have had for less than a year and they are starting to pill and look old. They are amazing but do not last

These are amazing!! They seriously do fit like a second skin, they look amazing wash after wash, never fade. I was tired of searching for leggings that weren’t see through and these have finally passed the test!!

column5: So comfortable but pilled quickly - not worth price
column6:
I really wanted to love these and had such high hopes. This is my first pair of Lululemons and I got a lot of input from the salesperson, who was super nice but seems to have oversold the quality of the leggings. I had tried on Aligns and Wunder Unders - I tried both the Luon and Luxtreme fabrics in the Wunder Unders and decided to go with the Luon. I liked both but slightly leaned towards the Luon since it was matte and would go more with my everyday clothes. The deciding factor was that the sales associate said the Luon material would take YEARS to pill as long as I washed in cold and hung dry (and she said the Luxtreme would NEVER pill - is that true?). So I went with the Luon since I figured I would get years of wear out of it before it pilled.
Well, I've worn the leggings about 5 times over the past few weeks that I've owned them and it's already pilling. I've only done errands and no workouts in them :( Even though they are insanely comfortable, I wouldn't pay $100 for leggings that pill after a few wears. My $20 TJMaxx leggings have worn much better than these. I totally thought I would join the Lulu cult for a hot minute because the leggings DO feel very good, but am sorely disappointed. I'd be willing to pay for truly high quality things, but unfortunately these are not it.

column6: Do not buy these for any physical activity! I bought these for my 14 year old daughter 3 weeks ago. She has worn them about 5 times. In gym class yesterday, she went down to her knees, on a polished wood floor (not cement), stood up and has 2 huge holes in the knees. When I brought them back to the store, inquiring about the durability, the associate (who was extremely kind and apologetic) said that the guarantee/warranty only extends to manufacturer defects, not wear and tear. If the leggings were a year or more old, I would understand that the fabric in the knees was a little more stressed and could easily tear (hence, the 'wear and tear' logic). I do not expect this from 3 week old leggings that have basically only been worn to the mall. I would also expect this poor performance from cheap department store leggings - not ones that cost $100. I will think long and hard again before handing over that kind of money for the sub-quality material that these seem to be made of. I guess they're good for walking and not much else.

column6: I have three pairs of high-waisted Wunder Unders from a few years ago, two of the standard black and one grey pair in that lovely cotton fabric you used to sell. They've all held up beautifully, still soft and thick and just as stretchy as when they were new. I wanted to add to my collection, so I ordered another black pair online. I've been buying Lululemon since you only had one store on 4th in Vancouver, and have watched the quality slowly take a dive over the years, but your products were still acceptable for the most part. However, this latest pair of leggings is going right back to the store. Thin, cheap, gross-feeling fabric, weird calf shaping to the legs, and they're at least an inch shorter in the waist than my old ones - they're barely high-waisted anymore (I'm comparing them laid flat from the waist seam to the top, so I'm not just getting fatter or something). Not worth $100 by any means. Never mind the time it took me to sort through your products to figure out what your "normal" fabric is called now, and what the heck is the standard pant length - different product pages with different lengths in different colours and different fabrics, no real explanation of how the fabrics differ. I was stupid not to read the reviews - nearly all of the most recent ones are negative. Lululemon will always have new customers who don't know what you used to be like, so I know you'll never hurt for profit, but maybe you'll eventually take these reviews seriously and make something worth buying again. In the meantime, I'll be treating my old leggings like gold and shopping elsewhere.

column5: Overall good but does stretch A LOT
column6: I'm a bit surprised with all the negative comments about these pants. I am about to purchase another pair in a smaller size as they're so comfy and flattering. My current pair I've had for a year and I have no issues with piling or seams coming apart and I wear these A LOT! I have noticed a small bit of piling between the thighs but that's because I wear these all the time for spinning. I wash these in the machine on delicate and used to leave to dry naturally. The only disappointing thing is that they do stretch a lot, so I would recommend going a size down or even two. They've stretched so much that I now tumble dry them to see if I can shrink them (they don't shrink). Please Lulu Lemon, sort the stretching out and these would be THE PERFECT legging.

I am extremely disappointed with my last purchase. I bought these pants last week and today was the first day wearing them for a light workout at the gym. I do not enjoy going aroun the gym showing the map of my private parts. Moreover, 20 minutes after I finished my workout the sweat was still visible, fast dry "forget it". I am back to the store to return these pants. Worst pants ever, not even my cheapest black pants are like these wunder under pants.

column6:
I can literally do anything in these pants! I can go to the gym, sit in my lectures, and even wear them under my scrub pants! They fit great in my legs, butt, and waist, and I certainly am a fan of the high-waisted aspect of these pants.
They're comfortable and seriously make you feel like taking over the world just got a little easier.

I bought these pants thinking they would be like all the other Lulu pants I have. I have been shopping at Lulu Lemon for a decade and they have always had really high quality activewear. They have started making a lot of new pants some great, some not so great. Yes I like that these are high rise and black pants but they are thin and I had to send the first pair back with a hole...Now i have had the second pair for about 4 months and they are pilling in the thighs. The girls at the store have now told me some of the materials are for specific workouts. Thinner material pants are ok for Yoga or just hanging out in your house but when your hitting the gym hard or running they will pill and won't stand up. Like I said I have been buying pants from Lulu for a long time and its really disappointing that now I have to make sure my pants are made for my specific activity, maybe that should be on the tag or something. For pants that are minimum $100 I think I should be able to wear them pretty much for any activity, haven't heard of this issue with any other brand of activewear.
